Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mild hyperchloremia. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), but no evidence of infection. HbA1c is low despite glycosuria, which may indicate renal glycosuria or possible analytical error. Findings are consistent with renal dysfunction, likely chronic, with possible tubular involvement. Clinical correlation and further nephrological evaluation are recommended.
